=== Sleep ===

Disable enemies:
* Puts enemies to sleep
* They can't act while asleep
* Physical attack wakes them
* Useful for crowd control

=== Surround ===

Evasion debuff:
* Lowers enemy hit rate
* Enemies miss more often
* Stacks somewhat
* Great for tough fights

=== Defense ===

Single ally buff:
* Raises one ally's defense
* Moderate improvement
* Lasts entire battle
* Use on vulnerable characters

=== Increase ===

Party defense buff:
* Raises entire party's defense
* More efficient than Defense
* Essential for boss fights
* Cast first turn

=== Repel ===

Encounter reduction:
* Reduces random encounters
* Based on party level vs enemy
* Doesn't work on stronger foes
* Useful for exploration

=== RobMagic ===

MP theft:
* Steals enemy MP
* Costs 0 MP to cast!
* Amount varies by enemy
* Essential for long dungeons

